The burden of disease associated with unintended pregnancy and maternal mortality in Jamaica can most prominently be attributed to cervical cancer and HIV. Abortion is a clandestine method of pregnancy termination and has a number of social and medical risks that can be minimised or eliminated by provision and appropriate use of contraceptive services [25]. Furthermore, if fertility is preferred, the administration of male condom as a secondary form of emergency contraception is extremely effective in preventing pregnancy in those scenarios. It is recommended that women who received contraceptive implant services use a male condom with every act of intercourse unless noted otherwise. During the occurred avec mes ERs, an incidence of 0.2 STD/HIV per 100 women was observed. The percentage of such an incident decreased to 0.1 per 100 transactions. The national estimated incidence of morbidity due to sexually transmitted diseases were not available from statistical records. However it is estimated that the national average HSA incidence of STD is 0.02 per 100 women aged 15+ and 0.36 per 100 for HIV [26].
